<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-27T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-27T21:00:00-05:00" n="222" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.796/350: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Drew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-27T22:00:00-04:00">May 27, 1941—10
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>85. Your 95, May 23, 8 p.m. Application to eliminate Quito from the
                            international run will be held in abeyance pending the elimination of
                            Sedta or further word from you.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>